						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vikrama-chōḷadēva: Year 3 = 1257-58 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is built in at the beginning and seems to be incomplete. It appears to record a gift of land made by a certain Āḻvi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikkiramachōḻa-bhuvanachchak[kiravartti] in favour of the <hi rend="italic">tirumaḍaiviḷāgam</hi> of the temple of Vīrachōḻīśuramūḍaiyār in Koḻumam in Karavaḻi-nāḍu. Also mentions the village of Ōḍattuṟai.</p>						

						</summary>
